{
  "text": "Cre/\u03e9 ;Brn3b Zdta/\u03e9 mice in which most ipRGCs are eliminated, except for M1s that innervate the suprachiasmatic nucleus and intergeniculate leaflet [CITATION_1] . In these mice, we observed light-adapted b-wave facilitation that was similar to control (Fig. 9A, traces in third row, C) , suggesting that M1 ipRGCs are sufficient to facilitate light adaptation.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "19974439"
